3
00:01:28,036 --> 00:01:33,026
幾個世紀以來人們和巫師和平共處
For centuries man & mage lived together in harmony

4
00:01:34,027 --> 00:01:38,013
黑暗巫師莫德雷德的出現打破了這種平靜
until the rise of the mage sorcerer Mordred

5
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:42,084
人類成為了他邪惡野心的受害者
turning his dark ambition against man

6
00:01:44,012 --> 00:01:50,033
他正在向卡美洛進軍，那是人類的最後一座要塞
He marches on the last remaining stronghold Camelot

7
00:02:51,008 --> 00:02:53,075
烏瑟，這場戰爭我們沒勝算的
Uther, I don't think we can win this fight.

8
00:02:53,081 --> 00:02:56,012
我瞭解莫德雷德，他會接受我們的投降
I know Mordred. He would accept surrender.

9
00:02:56,018 --> 00:02:57,028
拿著王冠
Hold the crown.

10
00:02:59,058 --> 00:03:00,089
拿穩了
And hold it steady.

11
00:03:56,034 --> 00:03:58,061
沖啊！幹掉他們！
Drink their blood!

12
00:04:03,001 --> 00:04:04,002
戰鬥吧！
War!

13
00:06:06,054 --> 00:06:09,034
大家別忘了，在莫德雷德出現之前
Let us not forget that before Mordred,

14
00:06:09,041 --> 00:06:12,061
我們和法師們相處和睦
the Mages lived among us in harmony.

15
00:06:12,068 --> 00:06:16,008
我們之間從未起過任何衝突
Our relationship with them was always peaceful.

16
00:06:16,015 --> 00:06:18,022
直到一部分法師受到了黑暗力量的蠱惑
That was before they tasted power

17
00:06:18,028 --> 00:06:20,005
製造出猛獸，發動了這場戰爭
and produced those creatures of war.

18
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:22,095
錯的是他們的首領莫德雷德，而不是普通人民
But it was only Mordred, not his people.

19
00:06:23,002 --> 00:06:25,022
伏提庚，為什麼你要將所有的法師趕盡殺絕呢？
So why are we slaughtering them, Vortigern?

20
00:06:25,029 --> 00:06:27,036
難道王子殿下不會同情那些法師?？
Was not the prince friendly with the Mages at one time?

21
00:06:27,043 --> 00:06:29,033
我聽說他和莫德雷德相處過一段時間啊
Did he not study with Mordred himself?

22
00:06:29,039 --> 00:06:31,043
你想表達什麼？
What are you implying?

23
00:06:31,050 --> 00:06:34,046
我是受我父親之命出使
I was sent to study with him by my father,

24
00:06:34,053 --> 00:06:36,010
目的是鞏固我們和法師之間的外交關係
as a token of diplomacy.

25
00:06:36,017 --> 00:06:38,057
我們只想提醒陛下
We would only seek to remind Your Majesty

26
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:42,077
那把擊敗莫德雷德的聖劍，是一位名叫梅林的法師給您的
that it was a Mage, Merlin, who gave you the great sword.

27
00:06:42,084 --> 00:06:44,088
準備！
Light!

28
00:06:44,094 --> 00:06:47,041
要是沒有梅林和善良的法師們給予我們的幫助，我們還能贏得這場戰爭?？
Where would we be without Merlin and the Mages who helped him?

29
00:06:47,048 --> 00:06:49,098
那他們人去哪了？為什麼他們不現身呢？
Where are they now? Why do they not show themselves?

30
00:06:50,005 --> 00:06:52,032
麥西亞閣下，想必您肯定知道
You know where they are, Lord Mercia.

31
00:06:52,038 --> 00:06:53,098
他們怕受到牽連，銷聲匿跡了
They are running for their lives!

32
00:06:53,098 --> 00:06:54,075
別吵了！
Enough!

33
00:06:54,082 --> 00:06:56,022
放箭！
Loose!

34
00:06:56,029 --> 00:06:58,006
不會再有殺戮了
There will be no more killings.

35
00:06:58,012 --> 00:07:01,039
戰爭已經結束了，弟弟，聽明白了?？
There will be no more purges. Am I clear, brother?

36
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,040
散會
Now leave me.

37
00:07:16,068 --> 00:07:17,088
這樣的和平能持久?？
Peace?

38
00:07:25,002 --> 00:07:26,082
至少能有短暫的和平
For a while.

39
00:07:28,029 --> 00:07:31,006
是不是我們再來晚點，你們就要打起來了？
Have we arrived in time to save you from each other?

40
00:07:31,012 --> 00:07:33,023
只有你才能拯救我啊
The only person I need saving from is you.

41
00:07:33,029 --> 00:07:36,029
我可不是來救你的，我是來接兒子的
I came for the child, not you.

42
00:07:36,036 --> 00:07:38,073
你可不能把我的寶貝搶走嘍
Then you'll have to fight me for him.

43
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:40,080
我弟弟今天不太舒服
My brother's not himself today.

44
00:07:40,087 --> 00:07:43,030
好好照顧他，明天見
Look after him. I'll see you tomorrow.

45
00:08:10,013 --> 00:08:11,093
他們準備好了?
Are the men ready?

46
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,046
都準備好了
Yes, they are.

47
00:08:16,017 --> 00:08:18,047
大人，您確定要這麼幹麼
Are you sure about this, My Lord?

48
00:08:24,098 --> 00:08:28,095
我的妻子，醒醒，我要你按我說的做
Listen to me, woman. I need you to do as I tell you.

49
00:08:29,001 --> 00:08:30,065
發生什麼了？
What's going on?

50
00:08:30,071 --> 00:08:32,035
快起來，我們帶上兒子一起走
I need to get you and the boy away from here.

51
00:08:32,042 --> 00:08:34,022
我會儘快跟你們會合
And I'll join you as soon as I can.

52
00:08:34,029 --> 00:08:35,055
烏瑟，我很害怕
I'm scared, Uther.

53
00:08:35,062 --> 00:08:38,092
別擔心，這把劍會保護我們，我們快走
I have the sword. Hurry.

54
00:08:39,096 --> 00:08:42,029
親愛的，這裡是什麼地方
How do you know of this place, my love?

55
00:08:43,036 --> 00:08:45,063
我們這是要去哪？
You must tell me where we're going.

56
00:08:47,097 --> 00:08:49,027
為什麼你不說話啊
Why do you not answer me?

57
00:08:59,098 --> 00:09:02,038
我們到這下麵來乾什麼
Tell me what we're doing down here.

58
00:09:12,032 --> 00:09:14,099
親愛的，告訴我，這是怎麼回事
My darling, tell me what it is.

59
00:09:24,007 --> 00:09:26,000
告訴我，發生什麼了，我們一起想辦法
Tell me what it is, and I'll make it stop.

60
00:09:29,044 --> 00:09:30,071
沒事的
It's okay.

61
00:10:16,099 --> 00:10:18,026
解開纜繩
Untie the skiff.

62
00:10:44,045 --> 00:10:53,017
亞瑟王·鬥獸爭霸
翻譯：william2568

63
00:11:21,021 --> 00:11:24,007
倫底紐姆（今倫敦）
Londinium

64
00:12:59,055 --> 00:13:01,089
伏提庚王萬歲！
King Vortigern!

65
00:13:04,022 --> 00:13:05,056
別擋道！
Move!

66
00:13:08,043 --> 00:13:09,063
嘿
Hey!

67
00:13:31,032 --> 00:13:33,039
抓住他！
Come here!

68
00:14:07,095 --> 00:14:09,059
來啊！一個能打的都沒有！
Come on! Come on!

69
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:45,082
快跑，兒子！
Run, son!

70
00:15:56,046 --> 00:15:57,093
國王來了，讓開
Step aside for the king.

71
00:16:25,062 --> 00:16:27,006
讓他們回去工作
Get them back to work.

72
00:16:27,012 --> 00:16:28,006
是，陛下
Sire.

73
00:16:29,043 --> 00:16:33,043
士官長，維持秩序！
Sergeant! Get them under manners!

74
00:17:20,068 --> 00:17:23,071
陛下，您還是這麼英姿颯爽啊
Still so handsome, my king.

75
00:17:23,078 --> 00:17:26,035
水位怎麼下降了
Why has the water dropped?

76
00:17:26,042 --> 00:17:29,002
為什麼聖劍又現身了
Why does the sword reveal itself now?

77
00:17:29,009 --> 00:17:33,009
我還沒準備好，塔樓尚未完工
I'm not ready, the tower is not complete.

78
00:17:33,016 --> 00:17:37,086
在您的勢力增長的同時，反抗勢力也在積聚力量
As your power increases, so, too, do the forces that will oppose you.

79
00:17:37,093 --> 00:17:42,047
均衡之律不可破
Balance is a law that cannot be transgressed.

80
00:17:42,053 --> 00:17:45,037
合法繼承人將要回歸
The born king will come.

81
00:17:45,044 --> 00:17:48,017
這是無可避免的
It is inevitable.

82
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:51,021
我們說好了的
We had a deal.

83
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:53,051
當我摯愛之人的鮮血染紅這池中之水
When the blood of a loved one is spilt in these waters,

84
00:17:55,011 --> 00:17:56,045
我的欲望就能得到滿足
my desire must be met.

85
00:17:56,051 --> 00:17:59,052
的確如此，國王
There is no ambiguity, My Lord.

86
00:17:59,058 --> 00:18:01,072
我的承諾已經兌現了
We kept our side of the covenant.

87
00:18:01,079 --> 00:18:04,069
而您呢，您沒抓住那個孩子，那把聖劍您也沒搞到手
It was you who lost the boy, and the sword.

88
00:18:04,076 --> 00:18:06,026
我犧牲的還不夠多麼？
Have I not sacrificed enough?

89
00:18:06,032 --> 00:18:08,069
難道您的力量沒有增長?
And have you not felt your power increase?

90
00:18:08,076 --> 00:18:12,073
一個又一個王國臣服在你的腳下，您修建的高塔一層一層逐漸升高
With every kingdom conquered, with every level added to your tower.

91
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:15,067
當您用產自高盧(現法國)的白銀裝飾塔頂
When it is capped with the silver from Gaul,

92
00:18:15,073 --> 00:18:18,017
您會得到你想要的一切
you will have what you wanted.

93
00:18:20,054 --> 00:18:22,041
找到那個男孩
Find the boy.

94
00:18:22,047 --> 00:18:23,081
殺掉他
Kill him.

95
00:18:23,088 --> 00:18:27,041
您就能掌控聖劍之力
And the sword will answer only to you.

96
00:18:27,048 --> 00:18:30,035
如果還需要我助您一臂之力
If you desire further help,

97
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:32,068
您清楚所要付出的代價的
you know the price.

98
00:18:38,002 --> 00:18:40,049
今天早上偶然遇到了那幫維京人
Bumped into the Vikings this morning.

99
00:18:40,056 --> 00:18:42,089
他們堅持要我把這個帶給你
They insisted I give you this

100
00:18:43,076 --> 00:18:46,056
還有，他們向你表示深深的歉意
with their deepest apologies.

101
00:18:50,030 --> 00:18:51,070
用這些錢，好好照顧自己
Get yourself well.

102
00:18:51,077 --> 00:18:53,040
亞瑟，你犯不著趟這渾水的
This wasn't your responsibility, Arthur.

103
00:18:53,047 --> 00:18:55,047
別說傻話
Don't be silly.

104
00:18:55,054 --> 00:18:57,058
我的小時候你們很關照我
You girls have looked after me for a lot longer than

105
00:18:57,058 --> 00:18:58,058
而我原來沒幫到你們什麼
I've looked after you.

106
00:18:58,064 --> 00:19:00,038
現在我要報答你們了
I owe you everything.

107
00:19:02,045 --> 00:19:03,091
你笑什麼呢
What's so funny?

108
00:19:03,098 --> 00:19:06,032
我想知道你是怎麼從那幫人手上搞到錢的
I just wanna know how you get money out of Vikings.

109
00:19:07,088 --> 00:19:09,072
直接開口問他們要就好了啊
You ask them for it.

110
00:19:11,015 --> 00:19:13,009
快開門！
Open the door!

111
00:19:13,015 --> 00:19:14,009
嘿
Hey.

112
00:19:14,016 --> 00:19:16,003
我們奉吾王之命搜查這裡，快開門！
Open in the name of the king!

113
00:19:16,009 --> 00:19:18,026
把門打開
Open it.

114
00:19:19,020 --> 00:19:20,053
各位有何貴幹？
Yes, gentlemen?

115
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:23,013
有一個反叛分子往這個方向逃了，我們要挨家挨戶的搜
A turner come down this way. We're searching all houses.

116
00:19:23,020 --> 00:19:25,077
喲喲喲，新兵蛋子們，別亂來
Whoa. Slow down, new boy, before you trip up.

117
00:19:25,084 --> 00:19:28,000
你說什麼？
What did you say?

118
00:19:28,007 --> 00:19:29,097
我們可不是好惹的，你的這隻手不想要了是吧
I'm gonna take your hands for that.

119
00:19:30,004 --> 00:19:31,021
軍士長！
Sergeant!

120
00:19:33,008 --> 00:19:36,008
我不是跟你說過了?，別在這撒野
What did I tell you about this establishment?

121
00:19:36,015 --> 00:19:37,018
長官，是他先碰我的
He touched me, sir.

122
00:19:37,025 --> 00:19:39,002
那麼這是你運氣好，只是碰了你一下
Well, you should count yourself lucky.

123
00:19:39,008 --> 00:19:41,049
換成其他人的話，只怕會被打殘嘍
Most people have to pay for that.

124
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:44,066
帶上你手下的人，滾出去
Now take your terriers and get out!

125
00:19:49,016 --> 00:19:50,076
您就是“傑克之眼”吧，久仰您的大名啊
Jack's Eye.

126
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:52,096
發生什麼事了？
What did he want in here?

127
00:19:53,003 --> 00:19:55,067
反抗勢力又開始活躍起來了
Resistance are on the move again.

128
00:19:55,073 --> 00:19:58,004
前不久他們在河的上游襲擊了我們的一艘船
Hit a branding barge upriver.

129
00:19:59,050 --> 00:20:02,077
最近你有見過新面孔?？
Anyone in the house you don't know?

130
00:20:02,084 --> 00:20:05,091
傑克，這很難說啊，我們這是風月場所，人來人往的
Well, I'm not sure, Jack. People come and go.

131
00:20:05,098 --> 00:20:07,095
不過你放心，我們肯定不會跟那些叛亂分子同流合污的
But we don't fall that side.

132
00:20:08,001 --> 00:20:10,005
我姑且相信你，不過，這也只是你的一面之詞啊
Ah, well, that's as may be.

133
00:20:11,071 --> 00:20:13,028
我們會將這些叛亂分子趕盡殺絕
Well, they fall where they fall.

134
00:20:13,035 --> 00:20:16,065
這個所謂的“合法繼承人”肯定不是什麼好兆頭
This "born king" bollocks isn't good for anyone.

135
00:20:16,072 --> 00:20:18,012
我帶人搜查一下，可以吧？
Mind if I take a look?

136
00:20:20,066 --> 00:20:21,093
他受了傷，正在流血
He's bleeding.

137
00:20:23,066 --> 00:20:26,033
逃走的時候中了一箭
Took an arrow on the way out.

138
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:30,007
話說那個如果你們抓到了那個襲擊船隻的人，他會有什麼下場？
What would happen to a man who hits the king's barge upriver?

139
00:20:30,013 --> 00:20:31,087
你應該知道吧，那他有的罪受了
Well, you know what would happen.

140
00:20:34,014 --> 00:20:36,021
先是嚴刑拷打，然後再處決
And it doesn't happen quickly.

141
00:20:36,027 --> 00:20:38,054
如果有人窩藏他呢，那會有什麼後果
What would happen to the people harboring such a man?

142
00:20:38,061 --> 00:20:41,048
他們將受到同樣的懲罰
Well, they get treated the same as the man they hide.

143
00:20:41,055 --> 00:20:43,008
是?
Would they, now?

144
00:20:45,075 --> 00:20:48,055
那邊的老哥，看樣子你在這不太受歡迎啊
Not sure you're too welcome here, mate.

145
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:02,033
他們會好好待你的，不用擔心
You're in safe hands now, no need to worry.

146
00:21:03,037 --> 00:21:05,043
我們到後面的房間談談，快
In the back room, now.

147
00:21:05,050 --> 00:21:08,017
傑克，怎麼了，為何這麼緊張？
What's this all about, Jack? What's it got to do with us?

148
00:21:08,024 --> 00:21:10,044
你真的不認識這家伙？
Do you have any idea who that man is?

149
00:21:10,051 --> 00:21:12,084
我也很驚訝，他是大人物?，我居然不認識
For a man who's so popular, I'm surprised I don't.

150
00:21:12,091 --> 00:21:14,031
他叫比爾，綽號“肥鵝”(在英文中和“溜得快”諧音)
Goosefat Bill.

151
00:21:14,038 --> 00:21:16,048
我聽說過這家伙，他身手敏捷
I know who he is. He got that moniker

152
00:21:16,055 --> 00:21:19,008
無論你把他關在哪，他總能想辦法溜出去，因而得此綽號
'cause he keeps slipping out from the bars you keep putting him behind.

153
00:21:19,015 --> 00:21:20,032
我們在你這抓到了他
He was found in this establishment,

154
00:21:20,038 --> 00:21:21,085
這可於你不利啊
and that doesn't look good for you.

155
00:21:21,092 --> 00:21:22,072
到底是怎麼回事？
What's going on?

156
00:21:22,092 --> 00:21:23,072
什麼到底是怎麼回事？
What's going on where?

157
00:21:23,079 --> 00:21:27,032
亞瑟，我那邊有些人對你很有興趣，經常提到你
You've got some heat on you, Arthur. Your name keeps coming up.

158
00:21:27,039 --> 00:21:28,053
誰經常提起我？
In what circles?

159
00:21:28,059 --> 00:21:30,029
我說是市井大媽們，你信?？
My mum's sewing circle.

160
00:21:30,036 --> 00:21:34,097
我可是個黑甲軍軍士長，蠢貨，你覺得我跟什麼人打交道最多？
I'm a Blackleg sergeant, stupid. What circles do you think?

161
00:21:35,003 --> 00:21:37,053
現在告訴我那個叫露西的女孩
Now, tell me a story about a girl called Lucy,

162
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:39,004
那個維京人“灰鬍子”
a Viking called Greybeard,

163
00:21:39,010 --> 00:21:41,061
還有那個牆上的叛軍塗鴉，是怎麼一回事？
and some rebel graffiti dirtying these walls.

164
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:42,077
你是不是打算寫一部書？
Are you writing a book?

165
00:21:42,084 --> 00:21:44,081
把每個細節都滴水不漏的告訴我
Tell me. Every detail.

166
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:49,008
我們跟那些維京人好好談了談
We had a quiet word with a couple of Vikings.

167
00:21:50,031 --> 00:21:52,042
退後，別亂動！
Get back! Back!

168
00:21:52,048 --> 00:21:55,022
我說了，從頭開始講
I said from the beginning, the very beginning.

169
00:21:55,029 --> 00:21:56,029
我早上起床
I woke up.

170
00:21:57,049 --> 00:21:58,056
然後呢？
Then?

171
00:21:58,062 --> 00:22:00,032
然後我穿好衣服
Well, then I got dressed...

172
00:22:00,039 --> 00:22:02,029
我走下樓，看到那些女孩都在，但露西不見了
I went downstairs, I saw the girls. Lucy was missing.

173
00:22:02,036 --> 00:22:03,026
- 露西在哪？
- Where's Lucy?

174
00:22:03,033 --> 00:22:04,005
她是個好女孩
She's a good girl.

175
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:05,003
不錯的女孩
A nice girl.

176
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:06,050
然後呢
Then?

177
00:22:08,046 --> 00:22:10,030
然後我跟這裡這位管賬的
Then, me and the lads took care of a bit of business.

178
00:22:10,037 --> 00:22:11,043
談了會生意
Bit of housekeeping.

179
00:22:11,050 --> 00:22:12,064
賬都對了?？
Everything as it should be?

180
00:22:12,070 --> 00:22:14,024
這些是從那些船上搞來的
That's the spoil from the boats.

181
00:22:14,031 --> 00:22:15,006
然後呢
Then?

182
00:22:15,087 --> 00:22:17,027
昨晚喬治又惹事了
George had trouble again last night.

183
00:22:17,034 --> 00:22:18,081
好吧，去找他，我們前門見
All right, meet me out the front.

184
00:22:18,088 --> 00:22:20,058
哪個喬治？暴脾氣的喬治？
Which George? King George? Angry George?

185
00:22:20,064 --> 00:22:22,085
有龍紋身的喬治？亞瑟，說清楚點，到底是哪個喬治？
George of the Dragon? Be clear, Arthur. Which George?

186
00:22:22,091 --> 00:22:23,098
這附近也就一個叫喬治的
Our George.

187
00:22:24,005 --> 00:22:26,025
就是那個教功夫的喬治
Chinese George, Kung-Fu George.

188
00:22:27,095 --> 00:22:28,089
我們聽說他惹上了
We heard he'd had some trouble with the...

189
00:22:28,095 --> 00:22:30,019
維京人
Vikings.

190
00:22:30,025 --> 00:22:32,026
那就是幫沒教養的家伙
Well, none of them are house-trained.

191
00:22:32,032 --> 00:22:33,006
我記得叫你口頭警告過他們了吧
I thought you'd warned them.

192
00:22:33,006 --> 00:22:35,006
是啊，但他們英語說得不太好
I did. They don't speak English good.

193
00:22:35,013 --> 00:22:36,039
只怕他們的英語說得比你溜
They speak it better than you.

194
00:22:36,046 --> 00:22:38,030
等等，再往前
Hold up, hold up. Back up.

195
00:22:38,036 --> 00:22:40,087
在去見喬治的路上，你沒遇到別人?？
Are you sure you didn't see someone else before you saw George?

196
00:22:41,087 --> 00:22:42,093
- 早上好，亞瑟
- Morning, Art.

197
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,080
我們遇到了麥克
We saw Mike.

198
00:22:44,087 --> 00:22:46,014
- 早上好，麥克
- All right, Mike.

199
00:22:46,020 --> 00:22:47,054
哪個麥克？打鐵的麥克？還是屠夫麥克？
Mike the Spike? Kosher Mike? Which Mike?

200
00:22:47,061 --> 00:22:48,087
你老問這些無意義的問題，都快把我搞暈了
You're giving me a headache.

201
00:22:48,094 --> 00:22:50,098
就是那個扁鼻子麥克
Flat-Nose Mike.

202
00:22:51,004 --> 00:22:52,081
他一直在我們的地盤走私毛皮，一直沒交保護費
He was trafficking furs through our vicinity without paying a commission.

203
00:22:52,088 --> 00:22:55,035
你今天運的貨比平常要多啊
That's quite a load, bit bigger than usual.

204
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:57,041
是啊，老闆臨時改變了計劃，於是就只好多運點了
Yeah, changed last minute. Just landed on me.

205
00:22:57,048 --> 00:22:58,088
- 多運點總比少運點要好
- More is better than less.

206
00:22:58,088 --> 00:23:00,088
- 是啊，麥克，多運點總比少運點要好
- More is always better than less, Mike.

207
00:23:00,095 --> 00:23:03,089
- 既然多運了點貨，是不是也給我們多來一點保護費啊，麥克
- More's definitely better than less, Mike. You've had a result.

208
00:23:03,095 --> 00:23:07,022
抱歉，亞瑟，我會補交的
I'm sorry, Art. It won't happen again. I promise.

209
00:23:07,096 --> 00:23:09,026
沒事，麥克
You're all right, Mike.

210
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:11,006
既然能當朋友，又何必樹敵呢
Why have enemies when you can have friends?

211
00:23:11,013 --> 00:23:12,016
你把收到的錢藏哪了？
Where'd you put the money?

212
00:23:12,073 --> 00:23:13,070
什麼錢？
Money?

213
00:23:13,073 --> 00:23:14,000
什麼錢？
What money?

214
00:23:14,006 --> 00:23:16,013
你沒有把收來的錢存在你的箱子里??
Did you hide it with the rest of your coffers?

215
00:23:16,020 --> 00:23:17,007
你到底想說什麼
You're all over the place.

216
00:23:17,007 --> 00:23:18,047
總是問這些無關緊要的問題
You can't keep your questions in a straight line.

217
00:23:18,054 --> 00:23:21,011
我正在回憶今天發生的事，而你老是打岔
I'm trying to tell a story here, and you keep interrupting.

218
00:23:21,017 --> 00:23:22,097
而且，你所說的箱子也不存在
Anyway, I don't have any coffers.

219
00:23:23,004 --> 00:23:24,071
你拿走了你的那份回扣
Once you've taken your share

220
00:23:24,078 --> 00:23:26,094
我這裡還有些人需要照顧，總之，最後一個子都不剩了
and I've looked after the weak
and needy, I'm left broke.

221
00:23:27,001 --> 00:23:28,038
繼續講麥克和毛皮貨的事
Mike and the furs.

222
00:23:28,044 --> 00:23:30,001
終於可以回歸正題了
So we're back to that story, are we now, Jack?

223
00:23:30,008 --> 00:23:31,008
麥克，你這是乾啥呢
What are you doing, Mike?

224
00:23:31,008 --> 00:23:32,012
您不是讓我交保護費?
Sharing the wealth.

225
00:23:32,018 --> 00:23:35,018
錢別給我，規矩不是這樣的，給威特，他負責管賬
Don't pass it to me, Mike. It doesn't work like that. Give it to Wet Stick.

226
00:23:35,025 --> 00:23:37,025
我是拜克·萊克，把錢給我乾啥
I'm Back Lack. What are you giving it to me for?

227
00:23:37,032 --> 00:23:38,022
那到底要我怎麼樣
What was I thinking?

228
00:23:38,032 --> 00:23:40,052
你不懂規矩？錢別給我們老闆，他不管賬的
Don't upset the boss, Mike. He doesn't handle the money.

229
00:23:40,059 --> 00:23:41,092
抱歉，今天忙的我暈頭轉向
Sorry, it's been a long day.

230
00:23:41,099 --> 00:23:43,066
這才大清早呢，你就忙暈了？每天按時交錢，就不會有這麼多事了
It's first thing in the morning, Mike.

231
00:23:43,073 --> 00:23:44,053
最後你們收到了錢?？
Did he pay?

232
00:23:44,073 --> 00:23:46,053
當然，那個麥克可是個老實人
'Course he paid. He's a good boy, that Mike.

233
00:23:46,060 --> 00:23:48,093
拿好零錢，找個人好好教教你道上的規矩
Buy some lessons in street etiquette with the change.

234
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,087
- 那零錢呢？ - 麥克，我們不找零
- Change? - There's no change, Mike.

235
00:23:50,093 --> 00:23:51,087
回見，麥克
See you later, Mike.

236
00:23:51,087 --> 00:23:52,080
再見，麥克
Cheers, Mike!

237
00:23:52,087 --> 00:23:53,097
天，這幫人真難纏
God.

238
00:23:54,004 --> 00:23:55,057
傑克，你還想問什麼？
What is this about, Jack?

239
00:23:55,064 --> 00:23:58,034
還有那個小男孩畫的反動塗鴉
Rebel graffiti. A young boy.

240
00:23:58,041 --> 00:24:00,008
沒搞錯的話，應該就是你的兒子布魯畫的吧
Your boy. Blue Boy.

241
00:24:00,014 --> 00:24:01,061
別搞錯了，他可是個好孩子
And he's a good boy.

242
00:24:01,068 --> 00:24:03,021
你們這些小屁孩在乾啥呢
Oi! What are you lot doing?

243
00:24:03,028 --> 00:24:05,065
傑克，不要妄加揣測
Don't start getting the wrong end of the stick, Jack.

244
00:24:05,072 --> 00:24:07,018
他跟那些叛亂分子毫無瓜葛
He's an upstanding citizen.

245
00:24:07,025 --> 00:24:08,088
萊克，你最好管管你家的小東西
I think I found something that belongs to you, Lack.

246
00:24:08,095 --> 00:24:10,045
小混蛋，你在乾啥呢？
What you doing, boy?

247
00:24:10,052 --> 00:24:11,059
他馬上就要回來了
He's coming back.

248
00:24:11,065 --> 00:24:12,089
你說誰要回來了？
Who's coming back?

249
00:24:12,096 --> 00:24:14,032
那個“合法繼承人”
The born king.

250
00:24:14,039 --> 00:24:16,033
是啊是啊，等他回來了，肯定會打你的屁股
Yeah, and when he does, he'll spank your arse.

251
00:24:16,039 --> 00:24:18,064
趕緊把手洗乾凈，要是被黑甲軍看見你在畫塗鴉
Now, let's get your hands clean while you still got some.

252
00:24:18,066 --> 00:24:20,043
他們會把你抓走，把你的手給剁嘍
He'll cut 'em off and have you in chains.

253
00:24:20,050 --> 00:24:22,043
這次只是被我們撞見了，下次可就說不准了
If we can catch you, they can catch you.

254
00:24:22,050 --> 00:24:24,023
最好別讓我手下的人抓到他在畫塗鴉
If you can catch him, so can we.

255
00:24:24,030 --> 00:24:25,070
我們繼續講喬治的事，他跟維京人
Should we go back to George, and the trouble with the...

256
00:24:25,077 --> 00:24:26,047
有點過節
Vikings.

257
00:24:26,047 --> 00:24:27,017
發生什麼事了？
So what happened?

258
00:24:27,024 --> 00:24:28,094
這些人欺人太甚
Started throwing their weight about

259
00:24:29,001 --> 00:24:31,024
- 他們把露西打了一頓 - 你說什麼？
- and then Lucy got the worst of it. - Come again, George?

260
00:24:31,031 --> 00:24:32,008
他們打傷了露西
They hurt Lucy.

261
00:24:32,091 --> 00:24:33,098
傑克，欺負我的人，這可不行
That can't happen, Jack.

262
00:24:34,005 --> 00:24:35,025
傑克，這絕對不行
That can never happen, Jack.

263
00:24:35,031 --> 00:24:36,055
她是我的朋友
You see, she's a friend of mine.

264
00:24:36,058 --> 00:24:38,018
所以你們既然傷了她，那就給她錢作為補償
So you're gonna have to sort her out.

265
00:24:38,025 --> 00:24:40,028
我們已經警告過他們不要動手傷人了，那他們這次就要付出代價了
They'd been warned. They had to pay.

266
00:24:40,035 --> 00:24:42,065
你怎麼從維京人手上搞到錢的？
How'd you get money from a Viking?

267
00:24:42,072 --> 00:24:44,052
怎麼老有人問這麼搞笑的問題
I feel a joke coming on here.

268
00:24:44,059 --> 00:24:45,082
直接問他們要就行了啊
You ask him for it.

269
00:24:45,089 --> 00:24:47,059
不賠錢，你們今天就別想走了
You're paying and then you're leaving.

270
00:24:48,093 --> 00:24:50,066
閉嘴，我沒跟你講話
Nobody's talking to you, sweetheart.

271
00:24:50,073 --> 00:24:52,063
你最好坐在那，把嘴閉上
You sit there and be quiet. You are better at that...

272
00:24:52,070 --> 00:24:55,006
然而他不聽勸，我們就給他大腿上來了一箭
Or I'll have to put an arrow through your lard-loving thigh.

273
00:24:56,053 --> 00:24:59,017
你不是沒帶武器?，你怎麼可能就這麼大搖大擺的走到他們面前，問他們要錢？
You were unarmed. You just walked in there and asked them for it?

274
00:24:59,024 --> 00:25:00,097
沒錯，傑克，我就這麼大搖大擺的走到了他們的面前，拿到了錢
That's right, Jack, and they gave it to me.

275
00:25:01,004 --> 00:25:03,027
他們披著今天早上扁鼻子麥克運的皮草
They were trying on furs. The same furs, as it happens

276
00:25:03,034 --> 00:25:05,021
正是麥克想瞞著我們偷運的那批貨
that Flat-Nose Mike tried to hide from us.

277
00:25:05,028 --> 00:25:07,031
多運點總比少運點要好，麥克
More is always better than less, Mike.

278
00:25:07,038 --> 00:25:08,098
然後維京人“灰鬍子”開始吹牛了
Old Greybeard banged on for a bit.

279
00:25:09,005 --> 00:25:11,022
我這有五十個身經百戰的戰士
I got 50 seasoned men of war.

280
00:25:11,028 --> 00:25:13,098
他們刀法了得，想要見識一下?
You could shave a pig on the edge of our blades.

281
00:25:14,005 --> 00:25:16,065
你說你沒帶武器，那你頂著他喉嚨的那把刀是哪來的？
If you were unarmed, where'd you find the blade to put to his throat?

282
00:25:16,072 --> 00:25:18,076
拜克·萊克一箭射中了那家伙的大腿，他痛苦的嚎叫起來
Well, I borrowed it from his big, silly mate

283
00:25:18,082 --> 00:25:21,046
然後我就把他的刀一把奪過來
after Back Lack put an arrow
through his lard-loving thigh.

284
00:25:25,076 --> 00:25:27,006
退後，別亂動
Get back!

285
00:25:27,013 --> 00:25:28,070
所有細節都告訴你了，傑克
That's your story, Jack.

286
00:25:28,077 --> 00:25:29,097
這事這麼著
I am leaving.

287
00:25:30,003 --> 00:25:31,097
你賠她一年的工錢，這事就算扯平了
But I'm leaving with a year's wages.

288
00:25:32,004 --> 00:25:35,011
“灰鬍子”同意賠錢
Old Greybeard surrendered his dignity.

289
00:25:35,017 --> 00:25:37,037
露西拿到了一年的工錢
Lucy got a year's worth of wages.

290
00:25:37,044 --> 00:25:39,058
再也沒人畫所謂的反動塗鴉了
And the rebel graffiti exists no more

291
00:25:39,064 --> 00:25:43,038
因為布魯和他的爸爸都是遵紀守法的人
because of the law-abiding, proactive Blue Boy and his fun-loving dad.

292
00:25:43,045 --> 00:25:46,082
最後，我們大家又可以過上幸福的生活了
And then, they all lived happily ever after.

293
00:25:46,088 --> 00:25:49,079
亞瑟，事情沒有你想的那麼簡單
No, they didn't, Arthur.

294
00:25:49,085 --> 00:25:52,099
我一直以為你是個萬事通
Because for the first time, there's something you don't know.

295
00:25:53,006 --> 00:25:54,099
沒想到，還有你不知道的事
Something nobody told you.

296
00:25:55,006 --> 00:25:57,009
什麼事？
And that is?

297
00:25:57,016 --> 00:25:59,046
那幫維京人，可是受國王保護的
They're under the protection of the king.

298
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:06,054
你要是招惹了他們，恐怕沒好果子吃，到時候我可幫不了你
And once you're under the protection of the king, I can't help you.

299
00:26:06,060 --> 00:26:07,067
誰都救不了你
Nobody can.

300
00:26:09,061 --> 00:26:11,054
我覺得，他們大概也不會在意我這個無名小卒吧
They're not gonna bother about me.

301
00:26:15,008 --> 00:26:16,065
麥西亞，現在情況如何？
Where do we stand, Mercia?

302
00:26:16,071 --> 00:26:19,001
目前和他年齡相仿的人我們基本都找來了
We're down to the last men of the right age.

303
00:26:20,038 --> 00:26:22,005
還是沒有人能把那柄劍拔出來
And still no one has pulled the sword.

304
00:26:22,012 --> 00:26:25,016
卡蒂亞，把鳥放回籠子里
Now put the bird back in the aviary, Catia.

305
00:26:30,046 --> 00:26:34,000
不安的氣氛在民眾間蔓延
There's a general restlessness among the people.

306
00:26:34,006 --> 00:26:37,003
事故頻發，到處都有反動塗鴉
More incidents. More graffiti.

307
00:26:39,064 --> 00:26:41,017
陛下，請您原諒
I beg your pardon, Your Majesty.

308
00:26:41,024 --> 00:26:42,017
如果我早知道您光臨寒舍...
If I'd known...

309
00:26:42,024 --> 00:26:43,027
來，坐下
Come here.

310
00:26:43,034 --> 00:26:44,057
我要問你點事
I want your opinion.

311
00:26:45,081 --> 00:26:47,058
都說麥琪可以代表民眾的意見
Maggie represents the people.

312
00:26:47,064 --> 00:26:50,048
她出生於英格蘭歷史最悠久的家族
She's from one of the oldest families in England.

313
00:26:50,055 --> 00:26:51,078
她能夠解答我的疑惑
She can tell us.

314
00:26:51,085 --> 00:26:53,005
大人，您想問什麼？
Sire.

315
00:26:53,078 --> 00:26:55,032
民眾們愛戴他們的國君?？
Do the people love me?

316
00:26:58,012 --> 00:26:59,079
陛下，我十分愛戴您
I love Your Majesty

317
00:26:59,086 --> 00:27:04,093
如果我可以代表民眾的話，那民眾都是愛戴您的
and if I represent the people, then you have your answer.

318
00:27:04,099 --> 00:27:06,053
給我們做點吃的吧
Bring us something to eat.

319
00:27:12,054 --> 00:27:14,004
其實我在想
Even I am left to wonder

320
00:27:14,011 --> 00:27:16,034
我們是不是有點做的過頭了
if we are pushing them too far...

321
00:27:19,088 --> 00:27:21,048
儘快把塔樓修好
Finish the tower.

322
00:27:22,055 --> 00:27:24,075
其它的都只是毫無意義的揣測
Everything else will be academic.

323
00:27:29,089 --> 00:27:31,019
謝謝你，麥琪
Thank you, Maggie.

324
00:27:49,064 --> 00:27:50,081
醒醒！
Wake up!

325
